    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-04-24T15:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-04-24T15:36:00-05:00" n="145"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d145">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/23709: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-04-24T14:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 24, 1920—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>138. Referring to telegram no. 114 from the Department, 14th instant, this
                    Embassy believes that the Legations of Great Britain, Argentina, Norway, and
                    Chile would be more generous than instructions permit American Embassy to be in
                    extending privilege of asylum.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
